Marten van Cleve. Reznicek, Mostra di disegni fiamminghi e olandesi, Uffizi, 1964, N° 26 (Fig. 27) old attrib. to M.v. Cleve. View of a Village with Peasants, Reznicek accepts the attribution & compares stylistically with Albertina drawing by M.v. Cl., especially Benesch, N° 88; In Uffizi another drawing by the same hand (Peasant dance in landscape, Inv. 632P) which is mentioned in article on M.v. Cl. (by Zoege von Manteuffel in Thieme Becker VII).
